    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-17T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-17T12:00:00-05:00" n="215"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d215">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">362.1121 Simpson, Lawrence/74: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Hamburg</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schnare</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-17T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 17, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to your despatch No. 499,<note n="8" xml:id="d215fn8">Not
                        printed.</note> please express to the appropriate German authorities, unless
                    you have already done so, the hope that Simpson may be given an early trial.</p>
                <p>The Department is likewise interested in knowing what measures have been taken to
                    assure Simpson of adequate legal representation.</p>
                <p>Please telegraph all important developments and supplement with full written
                    reports. You should also keep the Consul General at Berlin and the Embassy fully
                    informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
